00:56:51,775 --> 00:56:54,495
The idea was Z hadn't been
in the water for 10 years.

1176
00:56:55,045 --> 00:56:57,125
And so that was
such a big moment...

1177
00:56:59,216 --> 00:57:01,205
..and you had it be very serious.
He was, you know...

1178
00:57:01,652 --> 00:57:04,782
..considering whether to smack Cody
on the head...

1179
00:57:05,389 --> 00:57:06,699
..or go surfing and--

1180
00:57:07,057 --> 00:57:08,287
Just had him jump in the deep end.

1181
00:57:08,625 --> 00:57:09,675
-Yeah.
-Yup.

1182
00:57:09,993 --> 00:57:12,133
It came through Chad Stuart
animated that great shot...

1183
00:57:12,596 --> 00:57:15,906
.. where Z's upon the board
for the first time and he's tipsy.

1184
00:57:16,533 --> 00:57:18,673
It all came through right there.

1185
00:57:19,136 --> 00:57:22,566
We wanted to do--
Slow-mo photography...

1186
00:57:23,206 --> 00:57:24,726
is a big part
of surf documentaries.

1187
00:57:25,108 --> 00:57:27,658
The waves look so much better
if you're shooting at...

1188
00:57:28,178 --> 00:57:30,928
..200 fps rather than real time.

1189
00:57:31,481 --> 00:57:34,031
Again, Imageworks folks,
they pulled it off.

1190
00:57:34,551 --> 00:57:36,301
You're gonna see
a few shots coming up here...

1191
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:39,180
. that's just couldn't be
more beautiful.

1192
00:57:40,490 --> 00:57:42,830
Thanks to Sugar Ray
for this fantastic song.

1193
00:57:43,327 --> 00:57:45,697
And for Liza for bringing it to us.

1194
00:57:47,397 --> 00:57:48,857
Now, in this sequence, originally...

1195
00:57:49,766 --> 00:57:52,196
. Cody was gonna get tubed.

1196
00:57:53,136 --> 00:57:54,686
He was gonna find out
what it's all about...

1197
00:57:55,072 --> 00:57:56,592
..and he was gonna unlearn
that lesson...

1198
00:57:56,974 --> 00:57:58,724
.. that was much too complex.

1199
00:57:59,142 --> 00:58:02,602
I think we felt that just to be able
to hold on to the experience...

1200
00:58:03,246 --> 00:58:05,706
..that's transformative for him.

1201
00:58:06,216 --> 00:58:08,766
Yeah, if you got tubed this early...

1202
00:58:09,886 --> 00:58:12,226
.. then it said that he'd gotten past
needing to win.

1203
00:58:12,723 --> 00:58:15,353
If he went back to wanting to win,
then he hadn't learned a thing.

1204
00:58:15,892 --> 00:58:18,082
-So it was confusing.
-So we just keep it.

1205
00:58:18,562 --> 00:58:21,281
He has a good time out here,
but he doesn't get tubed.

1206
00:58:21,832 --> 00:58:24,491
Yeah, it's more about just getting
his confidence back so that he can....

1207
00:58:25,435 --> 00:58:26,895
That he feels he can really ride
these waves...

1208
00:58:27,270 --> 00:58:31,080
..and maybe has what it takes
to go compete now.

1209
00:58:33,810 --> 00:58:35,330
Now, where did the cannon ball
come from?

1210
00:58:35,712 --> 00:58:37,852
-Was that in animation?
-[ don't remember.

1211
00:58:38,315 --> 00:58:40,095
Was it--? Was it lvan?

1212
00:58:40,517 --> 00:58:41,567
Oh, Ivan suggested it.

1213
00:58:41,885 --> 00:58:44,345
-lvan Bilancio.
-Great moment.

1214
00:58:48,625 --> 00:58:52,315
The water in that shot even when
they're not waves, the refraction--

1215
00:58:53,697 --> 00:58:55,427
I just wanna dive in.

1216
00:58:56,299 --> 00:58:59,109
So this is probably, I would say...

1217
00:58:59,669 --> 00:59:04,058
.. the most complex story sequence
of the movie.

1218
00:59:05,609 --> 00:59:09,649
Z having to reveal what happened.
It was not easy.

1219
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:12,960
We had it earlier in the movie.

1220
00:59:13,650 --> 00:59:17,020
Or I don't know if it was earlier,
but it was in a different place.

1221
00:59:17,654 --> 00:59:20,144
How much to reveal?
How much to say?

1222
00:59:20,657 --> 00:59:24,027
We had one point when both
the characters were really angry.

1223
00:59:25,228 --> 00:59:27,038
-You kind of hated both of them.
-Yeah.

1224
00:59:27,464 --> 00:59:29,214
You really didn't care
what happened.

1225
00:59:30,233 --> 00:59:33,303
But somehow Z's journey
was about coming back to life...

1226
00:59:33,904 --> 00:59:36,974
..and returning to the beach
and to his--

1227
00:59:38,375 --> 00:59:40,485
His old friends and his family.

1228
00:59:42,813 --> 00:59:46,273
We let that fear of having lost
so many years ago...

1229
00:59:46,917 --> 00:59:49,787
..be the thing that keeps him
from being able to go to the contest...

1230
00:59:50,353 --> 00:59:52,873
..and support Cody
and be there for him, so....

1231
00:59:54,758 --> 00:59:56,508
-It was tough.
-Yup.

1232
00:59:56,927 --> 00:59:58,627
History revised,
we call this sequence.

1233
00:59:59,029 --> 01:00:03,539
And I think we revised this one about
1000 times.

1234
01:00:04,334 --> 01:00:07,674
It's such a delicate balance
on information in here...

1235
01:00:08,305 --> 01:00:09,325
..and tone for the movie.

1236
01:00:10,173 --> 01:00:12,542
Gets too deep and you start
to break the tone, the movie...

1237
01:00:13,043 --> 01:00:14,153
.. becomes more of a drama.

1238
01:00:14,945 --> 01:00:18,045
But there are some very big and
important things going on in this scene.

1239
01:00:18,648 --> 01:00:20,228
It turned out
to be the right moment...

1240
01:00:21,084 --> 01:00:22,924
.. for Z to reveal why he was
in hiding.

1241
01:00:23,353 --> 01:00:27,253
And that his fear of showing
his face again as a loser...

1242
01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:30,178
.. kept him from being able to go
and support Cody.

1243
01:00:30,660 --> 01:00:32,180
So they didn't pass.

1244
01:00:34,364 --> 01:00:38,204
God, it looks so easy now, guys.
We struggled....

1245
01:00:40,770 --> 01:00:44,720
Back to the archival footage.
Great grainy look.

1246
01:00:47,010 --> 01:00:49,260
Ash, you did some beautiful
versions of this...

1247
01:00:49,746 --> 01:00:53,466
..[ mean, going all the way back
to virtually the beginning of the movie.

1248
01:00:54,484 --> 01:00:57,144
-Well, we have--
-Yeah, it used to be in...

1249
01:00:58,021 --> 01:01:01,061
..in his tree, he revealed this,
didn't he?

1250
01:01:01,758 --> 01:01:02,897
Oh, really?

1251
01:01:04,127 --> 01:01:08,607
And even before that this is where
Geek revealed that he was Big Z.

1252
01:01:09,933 --> 01:01:11,893
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

1253
01:01:12,836 --> 01:01:14,236
Oh, this is the exact
same scene, right?

1254
01:01:14,604 --> 01:01:16,064
-That we used earlier.
-Yeah.

1255
01:01:16,439 --> 01:01:18,368
There's this spot lit....

1256
01:01:19,709 --> 01:01:23,109
So if you go back
and look at that scene now--

1257
01:01:23,747 --> 01:01:25,707
Back when Cody
first arrives in the island.

1258
01:01:26,149 --> 01:01:30,749
--you'll see Z backing off the board
and disappearing in the white water.

1259
01:01:31,855 --> 01:01:33,315
Not wiping out.

1260
01:01:33,924 --> 01:01:36,854
thought it would be kind of nice
to have a Zapruder like moment.

1261
01:01:41,131 --> 01:01:44,031
I mean,
I think our hats are off to...

1262
01:01:44,801 --> 01:01:47,411
-...our actors on this.
-Oh, yeah.

1263
01:01:48,605 --> 01:01:51,005
Yeah, we put Shia
through the ringer on this.

1264
01:01:53,009 --> 01:01:55,089
But he committed totally.

1265
01:01:55,545 --> 01:01:58,155
Well, every session we'd come in,
we probably had a new version of it.

1266
01:01:58,682 --> 01:02:02,162
And they'd keep asking,
"What was wrong with the old one?"

1267
01:02:03,253 --> 01:02:04,983
-They were troupers.
-Yeah.

1268
01:02:05,388 --> 01:02:08,258
But kudos to Shia, man.

1269
01:02:08,992 --> 01:02:11,332
He can handle both, you know,
the comedy and the drama.

1270
01:02:11,828 --> 01:02:14,638
-He can handle anything.
-Just anything we threw at him.

1271
01:02:15,198 --> 01:02:17,388
He's been an amazing guy.

1272
01:02:17,867 --> 01:02:20,647
So this is Cody's lowest moment
in the movie.

1273
01:02:21,204 --> 01:02:22,874
In case you hadn't noticed.

1274
01:02:24,307 --> 01:02:26,827
Well, you struggle with that.
It has to be somewhere in here...

1275
01:02:27,344 --> 01:02:28,574
..but you're not exactly sure.

1276
01:02:28,912 --> 01:02:31,692
Yeah, you question, when to--
When to do an interview...

1277
01:02:32,249 --> 01:02:35,709
..and when just to let the moments
play out without the interview.

1278
01:02:36,353 --> 01:02:39,833
But we really felt
we needed to remind people...

1279
01:02:40,490 --> 01:02:42,129
.. that he's are not just there
to win a trophy.

1280
01:02:42,525 --> 01:02:44,835
That there's
something deeper going on.

1281
01:02:45,328 --> 01:02:47,668
What he's really missing is a dad.

1282
01:02:48,164 --> 01:02:52,174
And what was a joke in the one
of the first sequences of the movie...

1283
01:02:52,902 --> 01:02:54,712
..ends up being,
as we kind of knew it...

1284
01:02:55,138 --> 01:02:59,118
..then really, just a core emotion
for this guy.

1285
01:02:59,843 --> 01:03:02,303
I think Cody's really been looking
for a chicken all his life...

1286
01:03:02,812 --> 01:03:04,422
.. more than a dad.

1287
01:03:04,814 --> 01:03:05,803
Like many of us.

1288
01:03:06,116 --> 01:03:07,786
-Great.
-Yeah, I've been looking.

1289
01:03:08,184 --> 01:03:10,814
-l'm still looking.
-How's lunch coming?

1290
01:03:16,326 --> 01:03:18,496
We won't ask how far the beach is.

1291
01:03:18,962 --> 01:03:21,272
Of course, it's right there.

1292
01:03:22,465 --> 01:03:25,125
The jungle set and the beach set were
two completely different models...

1293
01:03:25,669 --> 01:03:26,749
..and there was no way to--

1294
01:03:27,070 --> 01:03:29,260
We couldn't move
the camera around to show--

1295
01:03:29,739 --> 01:03:30,849
Show that the beach was close.

1296
01:03:32,942 --> 01:03:35,052
Now, this whole competition day
was inspired by a location...

1297
01:03:36,680 --> 01:03:39,140
..up in Northern California
called Maverick's.

1298
01:03:39,649 --> 01:03:41,549
Where Cody got his last name,
right?

1299
01:03:41,985 --> 01:03:45,615
Yup, we were-- It was that--
That documentary we watched--

1300
01:03:46,289 --> 01:03:47,959
-Condition Black.
-Condition Black, yeah.

1301
01:03:48,358 --> 01:03:51,668
Surfers going out in Hawaii
after a hurricane or--

1302
01:03:52,295 --> 01:03:53,555
They were gonna cancel it, right?

1303
01:03:53,897 --> 01:03:55,417
And the promoter wanted
to keep doing it.

1304
01:03:55,799 --> 01:03:57,439
Yeah, that was back in '74.

1305
01:03:57,834 --> 01:03:59,734
The promoter pushed the surfers out
against their will...

1306
01:04:00,170 --> 01:04:03,740
.. because he had a big, live broadcast
all set up to go.

1307
01:04:04,407 --> 01:04:06,807
That's right.
Didn't wanna have it cancelled.

1308
01:04:07,310 --> 01:04:09,390
So Reggie was inspired by that.

1309
01:04:09,846 --> 01:04:13,066
And if he's watching right now,
we apologize.

1310
01:04:14,484 --> 01:04:16,354
We hope you learned your lesson.

1311
01:04:17,554 --> 01:04:19,574
Without you, we'd never have been
able to get story point.

1312
01:04:20,023 --> 01:04:21,193
So thanks.

1313
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:26,380
I'm trying to think of all
the incarnations of this scene.

1314
01:04:27,097 --> 01:04:28,387
-l couldn't tell you.
-The whole--

1315
01:04:28,732 --> 01:04:30,662
Yeah, the fight Reggie and Lani
had about...

1316
01:04:31,101 --> 01:04:33,501
.. whether the contest
would proceed or not.

1317
01:04:34,003 --> 01:04:36,523
That's right. Man, I remember
this used to be like...

1318
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:39,850
.. 15 minutes longer
to set up the contest rules and--

1319
01:04:40,410 --> 01:04:42,899
Oh, we had the rules
and the scoreboards and all that.

1320
01:04:43,413 --> 01:04:45,283
And we realize that...

1321
01:04:45,915 --> 01:04:48,695
.. you folks, out there don't really need
all that information.

1322
01:04:49,252 --> 01:04:50,241
You already know this stuff.

1323
01:04:50,887 --> 01:04:52,257
If a surfer falls, you probably lost.

1324
01:04:52,622 --> 01:04:54,261
If he stands up on the board,
rides it, he'll win.

1325
01:04:54,657 --> 01:04:56,677
Those were our rules,
we decided.

1326
01:04:57,127 --> 01:04:58,857
That's all people really care about.

1327
01:04:59,262 --> 01:05:01,812
Now, this scene kind of
really happened.

1328
01:05:02,799 --> 01:05:04,939
-With our animators--
-Surf day.

1329
01:05:05,402 --> 01:05:07,012
Surf day out at Zuma Beach.

1330
01:05:07,404 --> 01:05:09,624
Not quite that size a wave.

1331
01:05:10,106 --> 01:05:11,186
Watching 40 or 50 people...

1332
01:05:11,508 --> 01:05:12,768
.. taking the same wave.

1333
01:05:13,109 --> 01:05:14,839
Wiping out all at the same time.

1334
01:05:15,912 --> 01:05:17,462
Hey, you guys came up with this.

1335
01:05:17,847 --> 01:05:20,457
-Little flashbacks, they're great.
-Flashbacks, great.

1336
01:05:20,984 --> 01:05:22,354
Just needed to get inside his head.

1337
01:05:23,853 --> 01:05:26,043
Yeah, you were doing something
unimportant...

1338
01:05:26,523 --> 01:05:29,183
. like you were having a baby
at that point, I think, and--

1339
01:05:29,726 --> 01:05:33,416
Not me, I won't take credit.

1340
01:05:35,565 --> 01:05:37,345
Great shot here.

1341
01:05:37,834 --> 01:05:40,493
-l love this.
-Not sure if he's gonna make it or not.

1342
01:05:43,940 --> 01:05:45,280
I love the soundtrack.

1343
01:05:46,075 --> 01:05:47,245
It was a huge moment for Cody...

1344
01:05:47,577 --> 01:05:50,357
..and we had to watch the music
still swell but we didn't get too big...

1345
01:05:50,914 --> 01:05:55,194
.. because it's not the climax
of the whole sequence.

1346
01:05:57,954 --> 01:05:59,854
-There he is.
-That was a late addition.

1347
01:06:00,290 --> 01:06:03,009
Oh, we struggled. Should we bring
him back, should we not.

1348
01:06:03,560 --> 01:06:07,070
Really hats off to Ash
on that one, we....

1349
01:06:08,364 --> 01:06:09,624
We weren't sure.

1350
01:06:09,966 --> 01:06:11,806
We kept thinking we could
bring him back at the shrine.

1351
01:06:12,235 --> 01:06:15,015
But it's nice to bring him back earlier.

1352
01:06:16,139 --> 01:06:17,839
We used to have a really extended--

1353
01:06:18,241 --> 01:06:20,111
-We showed everybody--
-Two minutes of--

1354
01:06:20,543 --> 01:06:22,093
--rising up through the ranks.
It's called that, right?

1355
01:06:22,479 --> 01:06:24,118
-Rising through the ranks?
-Yeah.

1356
01:06:24,514 --> 01:06:25,414
Oh, nobody care.

1357
01:06:25,715 --> 01:06:27,295
I just told you what you already knew
was gonna happen.

1358
01:06:27,684 --> 01:06:28,794
Exactly.

1359
01:06:32,689 --> 01:06:34,739
-Joe was enjoying everything.
-We knew from the beginning...

1360
01:06:35,191 --> 01:06:37,180
-...we wanted Joe to win the contest.
-From the beginning.

1361
01:06:37,627 --> 01:06:39,147
Just didn't know how
it was gonna happen.

1362
01:06:39,529 --> 01:06:42,279
Joe's gotta win. Joe's the guy
who doesn't care about it.

1363
01:06:44,067 --> 01:06:46,727
As his character developed,
it made more sense though.

1364
01:06:47,270 --> 01:06:49,990
l love Chicken Joe's surfing style
and that scene too.

1365
01:06:50,540 --> 01:06:54,580
It's like holding on to the rails
with his talons.

1366
01:06:57,814 --> 01:07:00,834
-Joe, typical Joe.
-Yup.

1367
01:07:03,953 --> 01:07:05,623
Again this is all improvved, right?

1368
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:09,622
Yeah, although they were
recorded separately, the kids, were.

1369
01:07:10,293 --> 01:07:13,893
Their agents and managers
would not let them work together.

1370
01:07:14,564 --> 01:07:16,703
So we had to record them
separately.

1371
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:19,554
And the hiccup was real too.

1372
01:07:19,936 --> 01:07:24,006
The hiccup-- I think this is when
Jeff brought the DAT recorder...

1373
01:07:24,741 --> 01:07:26,411
.. back in the first day.

1374
01:07:28,344 --> 01:07:30,974
And his son was just hiccupping,
and we go, "We gotta have that."

1375
01:07:31,514 --> 01:07:35,114
This was a late little addition, too,
but it's a nice touch of Lani.

1376
01:07:37,053 --> 01:07:41,942
Instead of just supporting Cody,
actually hurt by the whole thing.

1377
01:07:43,626 --> 01:07:48,196
That he would choose
to compete over Lani and Z.

1378
01:07:52,035 --> 01:07:54,555
Well, I like that story point,
it just holds...

1379
01:07:55,071 --> 01:07:55,136
.. that energy back
for the end of the story too when...

1380
01:07:55,138 --> 01:07:57,357
.. that energy back
for the end of the story too when...

1381
01:07:57,840 --> 01:08:00,710
.. everybody realizes
that Cody's triumphed.

1382
01:08:02,278 --> 01:08:03,328
I love that kind of decision.

1383
01:08:03,646 --> 01:08:05,046
One thing we never got
to make a point of...

1384
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:08,575
...was that surf board of Joe's,
it's an ear of corn.

1385
01:08:09,686 --> 01:08:11,706
Some bit of old wood
that fell of a barn somewhere...

1386
01:08:12,155 --> 01:08:14,205
..and turned it into this corn board.

1387
01:08:14,691 --> 01:08:18,260
Remember there was a long dialogue
scene with Cody and Joe here?

1388
01:08:18,928 --> 01:08:20,948
Where Joe is talking about
the meaning of life.

1389
01:08:21,397 --> 01:08:23,147
It got a little preachy.

1390
01:08:23,566 --> 01:08:25,265
Yeah, it got a lot preachy.

1391
01:08:25,667 --> 01:08:27,978
Much better for Joe to be
talking about kittens in the cloud.

1392
01:08:28,470 --> 01:08:29,640
Yeah.

1393
01:08:30,073 --> 01:08:32,293
A reminder of Z.

1394
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:37,543
That medallion came in
real useful.

1395
01:08:38,214 --> 01:08:40,434
It wasn't planned
that way, originally.

1396
01:08:44,020 --> 01:08:47,920
This used to go by so quickly
that-- A big moment--

1397
01:08:48,625 --> 01:08:50,645
-Tank wiping out, yeah.
-Weren't you guys saying:

1398
01:08:51,094 --> 01:08:54,554
"lL wish we could just replay it."
And we said, "We can, it's SPEN."

1399
01:08:55,465 --> 01:08:56,694
"It's animation. It's SPEN.

1400
01:08:57,033 --> 01:08:59,993
-We can do it."
-So here you go. So we did slow mo.

1401
01:09:00,937 --> 01:09:02,517
So anybody that missed
what's happening...

1402
01:09:02,904 --> 01:09:05,514
..we not only show them
we have Sal tell you.

1403
01:09:06,475 --> 01:09:08,965
But the energy that Sal
brings to this when you hear it.

1404
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:10,619
It's great.

